President Cyril Ramaphosa will on Wednesday participate in the centenary celebrations of late former President Nelson Mandela at Mvezo, Mthatha, in the Eastern Cape In a statement, the Presidency said the Mvezo celebrations for “the father of our nation and icon of the South African struggle” were organised by the Royal House of Mandela, in partnership with the Universal Peace Federation and the Eastern Cape provincial government. The celebrations to honour Mandela will bring together people from all walks of life, including current and former heads of government and state, traditional and faith-based leaders, surrounding communities, non-governmental organisations and members of civil society. Ramaphosa’s address at the celebrations will be preceded by various activities led by the Royal House of Mandela which include the handing over blankets to elderly citizens and bicycles to learners, as well as the unveiling of a sanitary towel project. READ MORE: CT Mayor De Lille and others join bikers for Mandela Day sanitary run The President will also open a clinic and attend a tree-planting ceremony. – African News Agency